#If the bill was $150.00, split between 5 people, with 12% tip. 

#Each person should pay (150.00 / 5) * 1.12 = 33.6
#Format the result to 2 decimal places = 33.60

#Tip: There are 2 ways to round a number. You might have to do some Googling to solve this.ðŸ’ª

#Write your code below this line ðŸ‘‡

print("Welcome to the tip calculator")
bill=float(input("What was the bill amount ? $"))
tip=int(input("What percentage of tip wpould u like to give ? 10, 12, or 15? "))
num_ppl=int(input("how mant ppl are going to split the bill ? "))
total_bill=bill+((tip/100)*bill)
each_pay=total_bill/num_ppl
round_each_pay=round(each_pay,2)
print(f"Each person should pay: $ {round_each_pay}")
